// prose.jsonl - hand-curated ground truth for the prose corpora.
// Each line: {"corpus":"<name>","query":"<natural-language>","expected":"<file.md>#<heading-slug>"}.
// Expected keys match embedProseCorpus's doc-name format:
//   <path-relative-to-corpus-root> + "#" + slugified H1/H2 heading.
// Slug rules: lowercase; runs of non-[a-z0-9] become single "-"; trim leading/trailing dashes.
//
// Queries are written WITHOUT library/identifier vocabulary (0k5h.8) so a
// model that simply memorised Go identifiers can't shortcut to the answer.
// A reader unfamiliar with this project should still be able to guess
// which document section the query targets.
//
// Comment lines (//) and blank lines are skipped by the loader.

